1
00:00:32,632 --> 00:00:37,934
EARTH ENTRANCED

2
00:02:55,675 --> 00:03:01,841
Eldorado Country in the Atlantic

3
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:07,547
Alecrim Province, Governor
Vieira's Palace

4
00:03:35,014 --> 00:03:35,742
Calm down!

5
00:04:09,382 --> 00:04:10,406
Any news?

6
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:12,777
The President demands your
resignation in five hours.

7
00:04:15,221 --> 00:04:16,119
Anything else?

8
00:04:16,356 --> 00:04:18,950
Federal troops
are going to Alecrim.

9
00:04:22,829 --> 00:04:24,194
I don't want any bloodshed.

10
00:04:33,072 --> 00:04:35,302
Now we have to go to the end.

11
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:37,839
The blood of the people is sacred!

12
00:04:38,077 --> 00:04:39,908
Blood isn't important.

13
00:04:41,314 --> 00:04:43,145
It'll be the beginning
of our history.

14
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:45,510
If we fail,
Diaz will rise to power.

15
00:04:45,752 --> 00:04:47,344
It's useless,
we'll be crushed.

16
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:49,111
You cannot betray! We...

17
00:04:49,355 --> 00:04:50,413
Our adventure is over.

18
00:04:50,657 --> 00:04:52,215
Adventure?
You call our work adventure?

19
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:53,550
Adventure...
adventure.

20
00:04:53,793 --> 00:04:55,055
You call it "adventure"?

21
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,125
Adventure!

22
00:04:56,362 --> 00:04:57,386
Sara!

23
00:04:59,532 --> 00:05:01,124
Write down what I say.

24
00:05:02,368 --> 00:05:03,562
Obey my orders!

25
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:05,566
Disperse any resistance!

26
00:05:40,239 --> 00:05:44,437
The contradiction
that rules our lives

27
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:47,510
has brought us to this
political stalemate,

28
00:05:47,747 --> 00:05:52,844
so familiar to those
who are engaged

29
00:05:53,086 --> 00:05:55,247
in great decisions.

30
00:05:55,488 --> 00:05:58,218
What is this document for?

31
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:01,621
It's about economic
and social development.

32
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:07,397
Thus, our fate is sealed,

33
00:06:07,633 --> 00:06:10,124
at the head of great
national decisions...

34
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:12,702
Speeches, principles,
promises...

35
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:15,373
We hand our government over
to the Supreme Federal Power.

36
00:06:15,608 --> 00:06:17,371
We're sure
that any resistance

37
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:20,272
would provoke a civil
war among innocents.

38
00:06:21,781 --> 00:06:24,045
Who are the innocents?

39
00:06:24,283 --> 00:06:26,751
I devote my path to God.

40
00:06:26,986 --> 00:06:29,352
And I hope God,
once again,

41
00:06:29,589 --> 00:06:32,524
blesses us with divine grace,

42
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:38,489
filling our hearts
with love and union.

43
00:06:40,733 --> 00:06:44,260
Do you see, Sara?
Who was our leader?

44
00:06:44,504 --> 00:06:46,665
Our great leader?!

45
00:06:46,906 --> 00:06:49,374
I used to say he was weak.

46
00:06:49,609 --> 00:06:50,940
The time had not arrived.

47
00:06:51,177 --> 00:06:52,667
The struggle would prove much!

48
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:55,244
People would die.
Blood, Paulo!

49
00:06:55,481 --> 00:06:57,881
History isn't changed by tears.

50
00:06:58,117 --> 00:07:01,518
If they take up arms,
if they do!

51
00:07:01,754 --> 00:07:03,187
Even people like you,

52
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:05,653
people like us, bourgeois,
weak...

53
00:07:05,892 --> 00:07:08,122
But I accept the risk.

54
00:07:08,361 --> 00:07:11,956
Stop, Paulo, your madness...

55
00:07:12,198 --> 00:07:13,825
My madness is my conscience,

56
00:07:14,066 --> 00:07:16,091
now, in the hour of truth!

57
00:07:16,335 --> 00:07:18,860
Time for decision!
Even in the face of death!

58
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:20,538
We don't need any heroes.

59
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:23,833
We might resist,
I need to sing.

60
00:07:24,076 --> 00:07:26,408
I need to sing!

61
00:07:31,017 --> 00:07:33,611
No more condecorations...

62
00:07:33,853 --> 00:07:36,447
This joyful pomp of glories...

63
00:07:36,689 --> 00:07:39,351
This golden hope on the Plateau.

64
00:07:39,592 --> 00:07:42,527
No more this regal parade...

65
00:07:42,762 --> 00:07:45,287
With war and Christ,
side by side!

66
00:07:45,531 --> 00:07:49,160
No more the naiveté
of faith.

67
00:07:49,402 --> 00:07:51,734
The impotence of faith...

68
00:08:13,092 --> 00:08:15,287
""I was not able to ratify
the treaty between

69
00:08:15,428 --> 00:08:17,293
the bloody cosmos and the pure soul.
A gladiator defunct, but intact

70
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:18,954
(so much violence, yet so much tenderness)
Mario Faustino

71
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:22,665
I' m dying now,
at this time.

72
00:08:22,902 --> 00:08:25,234
My blood and tears
are shedding.

73
00:08:25,471 --> 00:08:28,133
Oh, Sara!
They' ll say l' m crazy,

74
00:08:28,374 --> 00:08:30,899
a romantic,
an anarchist, as ever...

75
00:08:31,143 --> 00:08:34,237
I don't know, oh Sara...

76
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:35,340
Where I was 2,3,4 years ago?

77
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:39,807
Sailing with Dom Porfírio Diaz.

78
00:09:40,046 --> 00:09:45,416
The god of my youth,
Dom Porfírio Diaz.

79
00:11:23,816 --> 00:11:27,183
What I cannot explain
to my enemies

80
00:11:27,420 --> 00:11:31,618
are my reasons for abandoning
the pleasures of solitude,

81
00:11:31,857 --> 00:11:35,520
for the priesthood
of public life.

82
00:11:37,596 --> 00:11:41,862
But neither could
Christ explain,

83
00:11:42,101 --> 00:11:45,969
but by offering
His own life.

84
00:11:47,406 --> 00:11:51,968
And so,
I'd reply to my enemies

85
00:11:52,211 --> 00:11:55,612
that Christ gave
His life for the people

86
00:11:55,848 --> 00:12:01,047
when the exploiters wanted
Him to join

87
00:12:01,287 --> 00:12:04,154
exploitation itself.

88
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:09,326
He died, but didn't betray!

89
00:12:11,097 --> 00:12:17,935
Nor will l, by proclaiming
the greatness of man,

90
00:12:18,170 --> 00:12:24,302
of Nature, of God!

91
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:54,572
There he was, dancing
with Silvia, what a happy day!

92
00:12:54,807 --> 00:12:57,901
He was overwhelmingly
elected Senator.

93
00:12:58,144 --> 00:13:01,773
Such a happy day!
He was alone

94
00:13:02,014 --> 00:13:04,710
with Silvia and l, at home.

95
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:08,249
I was always following him,
almost lost,

96
00:13:08,487 --> 00:13:12,253
in those useless,
empty days in Eldorado.

97
00:13:12,491 --> 00:13:15,551
A hell called Eldorado!

98
00:13:16,896 --> 00:13:21,560
Frustrating,
stealing my youth.

99
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:25,362
I've been following
Diaz for years.

100
00:13:25,604 --> 00:13:28,630
And that night
he came to me

101
00:13:28,874 --> 00:13:32,469
so loving and tender...

102
00:13:36,682 --> 00:13:40,448
Our poet will be
elected deputy soon.

103
00:13:41,854 --> 00:13:45,688
To Silvia,
who will be Mrs. Paulo Martins.

104
00:13:52,865 --> 00:13:54,298
Aren't you happy?

105
00:13:56,068 --> 00:13:58,332
It's not that.

106
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:04,438
You know about my friendship
and admiration.

107
00:14:05,411 --> 00:14:08,676
But, starting with your help,

108
00:14:08,914 --> 00:14:11,644
when I could do it on my own...

109
00:14:11,884 --> 00:14:14,614
Don't you want to be
Dom Diaz's protégé?

110
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:16,879
Pride?

111
00:14:17,122 --> 00:14:20,683
I don't know, but,
it's my poetry...

112
00:14:20,926 --> 00:14:23,918
I myself, a new poetry...

113
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:27,496
If I could write about
serious things,

114
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:29,564
if I could talk about...

115
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:32,134
political ideas?

116
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:37,707
We're radical and extremist
when young...

117
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,110
I've been thinking...

118
00:14:43,048 --> 00:14:45,016
We don't have to meet again.

119
00:14:45,251 --> 00:14:49,551
You and your friends...
You and Alvaro!

120
00:14:51,924 --> 00:14:54,051
It was my decision.

121
00:14:56,962 --> 00:15:00,523
What can I do about Silvia?

122
00:15:00,766 --> 00:15:03,360
I don't know, I don't care.

123
00:15:03,602 --> 00:15:05,934
At least allow me this.

124
00:15:06,972 --> 00:15:09,634
Let me choose my own path.

125
00:15:11,610 --> 00:15:15,569
I've never been wrong, Silvia.
Never!

126
00:15:17,283 --> 00:15:21,515
Some day, one fine day...

127
00:15:30,296 --> 00:15:33,265
Good night. Excuse me.

128
00:16:25,451 --> 00:16:30,354
I see fields of agony,
I sail seas of denial...

129
00:16:30,589 --> 00:16:34,650
On my sword,
I bring remnants of passion,

130
00:16:34,893 --> 00:16:39,159
born in those wars,
some more, some less,

131
00:16:39,398 --> 00:16:45,667
cloistered witnesses of
the blood that sustains us.

132
00:16:54,213 --> 00:17:01,745
Death growing, flowing
and devouring.

133
00:17:12,898 --> 00:17:15,230
We live with death.

134
00:17:15,467 --> 00:17:18,959
Inside us,
death becomes the failure of

135
00:17:19,204 --> 00:17:22,367
our daily employment,

136
00:17:22,608 --> 00:17:27,944
as we advance, we retreat.

137
00:18:00,712 --> 00:18:05,206
"AURORA LlVRE" - AN lNDEPENDENT,
NEWS-PACKED NEWSPAPER

138
00:18:59,104 --> 00:18:59,832
Look!

139
00:19:00,072 --> 00:19:00,868
I see.

140
00:19:01,106 --> 00:19:03,336
Children without schools,
overcrowded hospitals.

141
00:19:03,575 --> 00:19:04,940
Look at this one.

142
00:19:05,177 --> 00:19:06,940
A campaign must be undertaken.

143
00:19:07,179 --> 00:19:08,373
Oh, my God, look!

144
00:19:08,614 --> 00:19:10,514
The donations aren't enough.

145
00:19:10,749 --> 00:19:12,307
Something must be done.

146
00:19:12,551 --> 00:19:15,349
We need a political leader,
that's it.

147
00:19:45,617 --> 00:19:49,553
""For the poor all that is offered
are scraps of fortune.

148
00:19:49,788 --> 00:19:53,280
Because no one will
take a stand to defend his kind.

149
00:19:53,525 --> 00:20:00,658
The orphan must have a home,
school, church and rights"".

150
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:04,025
Martín Fierro.

151
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:42,305
Someone like you could
never work for Diaz...

152
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:44,509
I owe him a lot,

153
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:46,677
you know...

154
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:48,777
Reading your article,
I never thought

155
00:20:49,014 --> 00:20:50,777
you could be so funny.

156
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:53,382
Funny, me? I am tragic!

157
00:20:54,186 --> 00:20:56,814
Sara also came to light Alecrim.

158
00:20:57,055 --> 00:20:57,817
Really?

159
00:20:58,056 --> 00:20:59,489
She's an efficient teacher.

160
00:20:59,725 --> 00:21:01,659
You're lucky to be with her.

161
00:21:01,893 --> 00:21:03,622
I really liked your last book.

162
00:21:03,862 --> 00:21:07,320
Youngster things...
Politics.

163
00:21:07,566 --> 00:21:10,660
I'd like to get involved
to politics.

164
00:21:10,902 --> 00:21:12,199
Really.

165
00:21:21,246 --> 00:21:22,770
It's a tough career.

166
00:21:23,815 --> 00:21:25,373
I came from the bottom,

167
00:21:27,085 --> 00:21:28,416
with my own hands.

168
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:31,756
Sara knows my struggle.

169
00:21:33,058 --> 00:21:35,253
I started as a simple
town councillor.

170
00:21:35,494 --> 00:21:39,794
I had to confront
cynicism, corruption.

171
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:43,527
Always the most noble causes,

172
00:21:44,770 --> 00:21:46,931
which are the hardest.

173
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:50,540
Mr. Vieira,
I think you're an excellent candidate.

174
00:21:50,776 --> 00:21:51,743
Fine!

175
00:21:51,977 --> 00:21:53,706
I offer you my humble services.

176
00:21:53,945 --> 00:21:55,503
He's formidable.

177
00:21:56,415 --> 00:21:57,507
To Vieira.

178
00:22:00,352 --> 00:22:07,349
The country needs poets.
The good ones,

179
00:22:07,592 --> 00:22:10,561
the revolutionaries,
like the old romantics...

180
00:22:10,796 --> 00:22:13,856
Voices that stirred the crowds.

181
00:22:14,099 --> 00:22:18,126
The streets belong to the people,
like the sky belongs to the condors.

182
00:22:20,072 --> 00:22:25,772
We'll hold big rallies
throughout Alecrim.

183
00:22:26,011 --> 00:22:27,740
Magnificent!

184
00:22:38,123 --> 00:22:41,559
Better days to the poor
and new life for all my people!

185
00:22:41,793 --> 00:22:43,522
So,...

186
00:22:45,163 --> 00:22:46,596
It'll be like this...

187
00:22:46,832 --> 00:22:48,356
Yes...

188
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:51,502
Viva...

189
00:22:51,737 --> 00:22:54,570
My dear, speak, don't be afraid.

190
00:22:57,309 --> 00:23:00,039
How lovely they are,
Your Grace. Write it down.

191
00:23:00,278 --> 00:23:02,269
Take note of everything!

192
00:23:02,514 --> 00:23:05,677
Take note.
All for you, my dear...

193
00:23:05,917 --> 00:23:07,475
Don't worry.

194
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:09,482
It's going to be all right.

195
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:11,188
Don't worry, go!

196
00:23:11,423 --> 00:23:16,827
Vieira, Vieira, Vieira...

197
00:23:27,038 --> 00:23:32,374
Quite! Quite!

198
00:23:33,845 --> 00:23:35,039
Mr. Governor...

199
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:36,577
Say, son...

200
00:23:36,815 --> 00:23:38,874
In the name of these people,

201
00:23:39,117 --> 00:23:42,177
I'd like to ask your attention...

202
00:23:44,956 --> 00:23:47,925
Water here, to wet our lands

203
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:52,790
Now, if you would, you could...

204
00:23:53,031 --> 00:23:55,261
you can, but...

205
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:58,560
My son, we're going
to stop these abuses.

206
00:23:58,804 --> 00:24:01,568
Write down, Marinho.
He's writing down, you see?

207
00:24:01,807 --> 00:24:04,332
Write down.
Isn't it, Your Grace?

208
00:24:05,777 --> 00:24:07,506
I'd like to say one more thing.

209
00:24:10,515 --> 00:24:12,710
Say it... Say.

210
00:24:19,991 --> 00:24:21,686
How is it...?

211
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:47,079
Attention!

212
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:52,757
My main objective is
to do peaceful work,

213
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:56,449
through free elections,
we'll lead to power

214
00:24:56,695 --> 00:24:59,357
the legitimate representatives
of the people!

215
00:24:59,598 --> 00:25:02,931
These representatives are

216
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:08,629
those who will fight
for the very needs of the people!

217
00:25:08,874 --> 00:25:11,638
Food, school!

218
00:25:24,256 --> 00:25:31,662
Vieira, Vieira, Vieira...

219
00:26:33,925 --> 00:26:35,722
And we won!

220
00:26:37,228 --> 00:26:40,322
What I saw in that campaign...

221
00:26:40,565 --> 00:26:45,332
A tragedy,
bigger than our strength.

222
00:26:46,671 --> 00:26:48,639
There,
on that calm veranda

223
00:26:48,873 --> 00:26:52,240
where we've planned
our struggle joyously,

224
00:26:52,477 --> 00:26:55,674
and then, at your side,

225
00:26:55,914 --> 00:26:58,940
I thought about possible problems

226
00:26:59,184 --> 00:27:03,985
and asked myself, "How could
an elected Governor answer

227
00:27:04,222 --> 00:27:06,918
to the candidate's promises?"

228
00:27:07,158 --> 00:27:10,958
Mainly,
I asked myself and the others,

229
00:27:11,196 --> 00:27:14,996
"How could we react to that?"

230
00:28:48,026 --> 00:28:51,518
'Cause our families arrived
in these lands,

231
00:28:51,763 --> 00:28:54,698
over 20 years ago.

232
00:28:54,933 --> 00:28:58,164
And we worked the land,

233
00:28:58,403 --> 00:29:04,831
we planted them and our wives
gave birth in these lands.

234
00:29:07,145 --> 00:29:09,807
Now we can't leave

235
00:29:10,048 --> 00:29:15,884
just because some "men"
appeared from nowhere

236
00:29:16,121 --> 00:29:21,684
showing papers and saying
they're the owners.

237
00:29:24,162 --> 00:29:26,790
That's what
I wanted to tell you, Sir.

238
00:29:27,031 --> 00:29:32,401
We trust you, but...

239
00:29:35,039 --> 00:29:40,875
if Justice says we have
to leave the land,

240
00:29:41,112 --> 00:29:45,742
we'll die, but we won't!

241
00:29:45,984 --> 00:29:50,387
Be quiet, Felicio,
show some respect for the Governor.

242
00:29:50,622 --> 00:29:54,786
Mr. Paulo, Mr. Paulo...

243
00:30:00,698 --> 00:30:02,529
We must shout!

244
00:30:02,767 --> 00:30:04,291
How?

245
00:30:04,536 --> 00:30:06,527
With whatever we have,
bones, everything!

246
00:30:06,771 --> 00:30:09,638
Shut up!
You know nothing!

247
00:30:09,874 --> 00:30:11,842
Mr. Paulo,
you used to be my friend,

248
00:30:12,076 --> 00:30:14,636
-you used to promise...
-I never did!

249
00:30:14,879 --> 00:30:16,471
I'm not a liar!

250
00:30:16,714 --> 00:30:19,205
You wretch!
Weak chatterbox! Coward!

251
00:30:19,450 --> 00:30:22,578
Mr. Paulo, don't say that,
Mr. Paulo...

252
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:25,051
Don't say that,
Mr. Paulo, don't.

253
00:30:25,290 --> 00:30:28,020
Mr.Paulo, don't say that...

254
00:30:28,259 --> 00:30:29,920
Do you see?
You're worth nothing!

255
00:30:30,161 --> 00:30:32,425
Mr. Paulo, you were my friend!

256
00:30:49,314 --> 00:30:50,906
I went there.

257
00:30:51,149 --> 00:30:54,550
I beat a poor peasant because
he threatened me...

258
00:30:54,786 --> 00:30:58,654
He could have cut my head
off with a hoe,

259
00:30:58,890 --> 00:31:02,883
but he was so cowardly
and servile!

260
00:31:05,230 --> 00:31:09,428
And I wanted to show
he was a coward and servile.

261
00:31:12,503 --> 00:31:13,902
Weakness!

262
00:31:17,342 --> 00:31:18,900
Weak people!

263
00:31:22,347 --> 00:31:27,341
Always feeble and terrified!

264
00:31:30,321 --> 00:31:33,154
