01:22:41,823 --> 01:22:44,553
and have nowhere to live.

781
01:22:44,792 --> 01:22:47,590
Extremist!
Extremist! Extremist!

782
01:22:47,829 --> 01:22:53,563
Extremist!
Extremist! Extremist...

783
01:23:06,647 --> 01:23:10,447
Hunger...
And illiteracy...

784
01:23:10,685 --> 01:23:13,586
are extremist propaganda!

785
01:23:13,821 --> 01:23:18,884
Extremism is a virus that
infects actions,

786
01:23:19,127 --> 01:23:21,994
infects the air, the blood,

787
01:23:22,230 --> 01:23:24,994
infects the water and morals...

788
01:23:27,201 --> 01:23:30,227
In Eldorado

789
01:23:30,471 --> 01:23:33,338
there is no hunger,
no violence...

790
01:23:33,574 --> 01:23:35,405
nor poverty!

791
01:24:36,337 --> 01:24:38,066
Political irresponsibility...

792
01:24:38,306 --> 01:24:39,466
Your anarchism!

793
01:24:39,707 --> 01:24:43,268
Political irresponsibility...

794
01:24:43,511 --> 01:24:44,603
political irresponsibility...

795
01:24:44,845 --> 01:24:46,005
Your anarchism.

796
01:24:46,247 --> 01:24:49,114
Political irresponsibility.

797
01:24:49,350 --> 01:24:50,749
Political irresponsibility.

798
01:24:50,985 --> 01:24:52,452
-Political irresponsibility.
-Your anarchism.

799
01:24:52,687 --> 01:24:55,952
-Political irresponsibility.
-Your anarchism.

800
01:24:56,190 --> 01:24:59,455
-Political irresponsibility.
-Your anarchism.

801
01:24:59,694 --> 01:25:02,822
-Political irresponsibility.
-Your anarchism.

802
01:25:03,064 --> 01:25:05,430
Enough!

803
01:25:13,541 --> 01:25:17,978
I'm almost 50 and I haven't
lost my dignity.

804
01:25:18,212 --> 01:25:21,409
Tell me, what you, Fuentes,
and the others want?

805
01:25:21,649 --> 01:25:25,210
I'm not here to be
a political clown.

806
01:25:25,453 --> 01:25:29,082
If you want power,
you have to bite into the struggle.

807
01:25:29,323 --> 01:25:33,225
I've told you,
inside the masses, there's man.

808
01:25:33,461 --> 01:25:39,923
The Man is hard to control...
Harder than the masses.

809
01:25:40,167 --> 01:25:42,101
No more reactionary theories!

810
01:25:42,336 --> 01:25:45,203
Reactionaries?

811
01:26:00,488 --> 01:26:02,479
We've gone too far.

812
01:26:02,723 --> 01:26:05,123
Maybe now it's late to go back.

813
01:26:05,359 --> 01:26:06,826
I understand...

814
01:26:18,472 --> 01:26:21,339
The trance of the mystics.

815
01:26:22,576 --> 01:26:26,637
Look in our eyes, our skin.

816
01:26:26,881 --> 01:26:30,339
If we observe it clearly,

817
01:26:30,584 --> 01:26:34,645
or only through violence.

818
01:27:09,724 --> 01:27:13,182
Every time I fought
for the underprivileged majorities,

819
01:27:13,427 --> 01:27:17,227
I was stupidly threatened.

820
01:27:17,465 --> 01:27:20,161
I stepped back many times,

821
01:27:20,401 --> 01:27:23,837
delaying today's
problems to think of the future.

822
01:27:24,071 --> 01:27:27,199
But if I send the present
to the future,

823
01:27:27,441 --> 01:27:31,935
I'll only find a future
drowned in tragedies.

824
01:27:33,147 --> 01:27:36,344
That's why I must now face

825
01:27:36,584 --> 01:27:40,418
Eldorado's enemies,
here and abroad.

826
01:27:42,022 --> 01:27:43,853
Unite the masses.

827
01:27:46,193 --> 01:27:48,058
Break away, once and for all.

828
01:27:50,398 --> 01:27:53,231
Cast off the boat!

829
01:29:08,542 --> 01:29:09,736
Do you know what he wanted?

830
01:29:09,977 --> 01:29:13,469
To use the press to support
the extremists.

831
01:29:13,714 --> 01:29:18,083
Use Vieira for this end.

832
01:29:18,319 --> 01:29:20,344
And where is he now?

833
01:29:20,588 --> 01:29:25,685
With the President,
saying Vieira leads the populace.

834
01:29:25,926 --> 01:29:28,258
The populace.

835
01:29:28,496 --> 01:29:30,930
Mr. Cassius visited me yesterday

836
01:29:31,165 --> 01:29:33,929
to say how disappointed
he was with you.

837
01:29:34,168 --> 01:29:36,500
He was the one who forced
the President

838
01:29:36,737 --> 01:29:39,797
to use freedom of the Press.

839
01:29:40,774 --> 01:29:43,436
But how could
I know you'd surrender

840
01:29:43,677 --> 01:29:47,408
to Paulo Martins madness.

841
01:29:48,616 --> 01:29:52,985
You know, Silvia,
why do they think we're irresponsible?

842
01:29:53,220 --> 01:29:56,986
Explint, for example,
helped you to buy the equipment.

843
01:29:57,224 --> 01:30:00,284
Paulo guaranteed me that
their competition would be disastrous.

844
01:30:00,528 --> 01:30:03,122
Paulo! Does he have
any political coherency?

845
01:30:03,364 --> 01:30:05,127
And Vieira is a democrat.

846
01:30:05,366 --> 01:30:07,960
Democrat!
He comes from the Extremist Party.

847
01:30:08,202 --> 01:30:09,396
You too.

848
01:30:09,637 --> 01:30:11,366
But I met God!

849
01:30:11,605 --> 01:30:13,835
I know,
but the cards have been dealt.

850
01:30:14,074 --> 01:30:15,666
We' re on opposite sides.

851
01:30:15,910 --> 01:30:19,903
Opposite!
Bravo! Bravo!

852
01:30:20,147 --> 01:30:22,581
Don't use this proud language.

853
01:30:22,816 --> 01:30:26,081
Because you're not prouder
or more impetuous than Paulo.

854
01:30:26,320 --> 01:30:29,881
Silence, Júlio.
Silence!

855
01:30:30,124 --> 01:30:33,491
Then, Álvaro came
to tell about the betrayal.

856
01:30:33,727 --> 01:30:35,695
Álvaro came as dead as me.

857
01:30:35,930 --> 01:30:38,922
He felt sick on blood.

858
01:30:42,736 --> 01:30:46,900
The revolutionaries...
A bunch of clowns!

859
01:30:47,141 --> 01:30:51,771
Do you know what the result of Paulo,
Vieira and the extremists' pact is?

860
01:30:52,012 --> 01:30:57,416
Vieira, once in power,
they will eliminate you.

861
01:30:58,652 --> 01:31:00,677
They don't respect pacts.

862
01:31:02,356 --> 01:31:03,948
I am left-wing.

863
01:31:04,191 --> 01:31:05,818
Left what?

864
01:31:11,398 --> 01:31:14,060
Look, idiot...

865
01:31:14,301 --> 01:31:16,531
The class struggle exists.

866
01:31:16,770 --> 01:31:20,228
What is your class?
Go on, say it!

867
01:31:27,948 --> 01:31:29,848
If we develop industry,

868
01:31:30,084 --> 01:31:32,314
create jobs, perhaps...

869
01:31:32,553 --> 01:31:35,716
Like starving beasts,
they'll want more and more.

870
01:31:35,956 --> 01:31:39,790
Even your own blood.
They want power.

871
01:31:40,027 --> 01:31:44,327
The people in power? Never!

872
01:31:44,565 --> 01:31:47,159
Understand? Never!

873
01:31:48,402 --> 01:31:56,070
For freedom, we' ll die,
for God, for power!

874
01:32:00,314 --> 01:32:03,010
How can I take power without
Paulo and Fuentes's help?

875
01:32:03,250 --> 01:32:05,241
Without the best men?

876
01:32:05,486 --> 01:32:08,080
Paulo betrayed me long ago.

877
01:32:08,322 --> 01:32:10,517
Fuentes is reluctant to support me.

878
01:32:12,860 --> 01:32:13,758
How?

879
01:32:15,896 --> 01:32:17,261
How can I explain it to my partners?

880
01:32:17,498 --> 01:32:19,159
You have to explain nothing.

881
01:32:19,400 --> 01:32:22,335
Let's take the power in a coup.
Change the game.

882
01:32:22,569 --> 01:32:25,538
Let's write history.

883
01:32:27,374 --> 01:32:28,432
But they have the guarantees.

884
01:32:28,676 --> 01:32:30,200
I have the guarantees!

885
01:32:31,245 --> 01:32:32,303
Which ones?

886
01:32:33,514 --> 01:32:36,950
By elections, Vieira wins.

887
01:32:37,951 --> 01:32:44,151
Without elections, I win,
overthrowing Fernandez.

888
01:32:44,391 --> 01:32:46,951
Only with your ideas?

889
01:32:48,362 --> 01:32:50,660
With Explint's support,

890
01:32:50,898 --> 01:32:54,299
by using its propaganda machine.

891
01:32:56,503 --> 01:32:58,403
Explint will pay.

892
01:33:00,607 --> 01:33:02,472
Paid propaganda.

893
01:33:07,915 --> 01:33:10,884
Then, Álvaro came
to tell about the betrayal.

894
01:33:11,118 --> 01:33:13,382
Álvaro came
as dead as me.

895
01:33:13,620 --> 01:33:16,384
He felt sick on blood.

896
01:33:16,623 --> 01:33:20,184
While the mini-genius of politics
was planning a revolution,

897
01:33:20,427 --> 01:33:22,054
Fuentes and Diaz...

898
01:33:22,296 --> 01:33:23,854
Fuentes and Diaz?

899
01:33:24,098 --> 01:33:27,659
together with Explint to defeat you,
Vieira and Fernandez.

900
01:33:29,369 --> 01:33:30,893
Did you see?

901
01:33:32,639 --> 01:33:35,437
With these blind eyes,
these dumb mouths...

902
01:33:35,676 --> 01:33:36,973
Look, Paulo,

903
01:33:37,211 --> 01:33:40,078
all I can do is to advise exile.

904
01:33:42,649 --> 01:33:46,449
And me, working night and day,
Fuentes...

905
01:33:46,687 --> 01:33:48,450
Your naiveté...

906
01:33:48,689 --> 01:33:52,056
So much work, so much effort...

907
01:33:52,292 --> 01:33:54,419
Actually Fuentes and Diaz
want you to quit everything

908
01:33:54,661 --> 01:33:56,094
and go back to them.

909
01:33:56,330 --> 01:33:59,663
And I am dirty, the monster?

910
01:34:01,101 --> 01:34:03,763
I don't know, I'm not interested
in your convictions.

911
01:34:05,773 --> 01:34:07,365
Your life interests me.

912
01:34:07,608 --> 01:34:09,940
What counts is that I am free!

913
01:34:10,177 --> 01:34:12,077
And I won't step back.

914
01:34:12,312 --> 01:34:14,371
Who's free? Who?

915
01:34:16,116 --> 01:34:21,281
Diaz. Diaz is.

916
01:34:22,289 --> 01:34:26,623
Your images, dreams.
You're a poor copy of Diaz.

917
01:34:26,860 --> 01:34:35,768
No. Diaz is my enemy.
He's not in my blood.

918
01:34:38,572 --> 01:34:42,099
It's too late!

919
01:34:43,710 --> 01:34:46,406
Maybe we can resist, with Vieira.

920
01:34:47,915 --> 01:34:50,440
He doesn't have the greatness
of a leader.

921
01:34:52,386 --> 01:34:56,686
Álvaro, I don't know, I don't know...

922
01:34:56,924 --> 01:35:00,382
Don't make me smash your face!

923
01:35:00,627 --> 01:35:08,659
Smash it! It's worthless. Smash it!

924
01:35:10,571 --> 01:35:15,531
I have no pride. No vanity.

925
01:35:16,977 --> 01:35:21,914
Nor ambition. Smash it!

926
01:35:37,965 --> 01:35:39,296
My friend...

927
01:35:57,284 --> 01:35:58,615
My friend?

928
01:35:59,953 --> 01:36:03,980
You were my friend?
I was your friend...

929
01:36:04,224 --> 01:36:06,920
But you took advantage
of my weakness

930
01:36:09,129 --> 01:36:10,858
and betrayed your style.

931
01:36:11,098 --> 01:36:13,066
React! React!

932
01:36:13,300 --> 01:36:15,632
React against what?
Against whom?

933
01:36:17,537 --> 01:36:20,028
Only you can react to survive.

934
01:36:21,074 --> 01:36:23,065
Call Fuentes, sell your soul.

935
01:36:32,419 --> 01:36:36,048
For Silvia, she loves you.

936
01:36:53,273 --> 01:37:00,805
Beyond hate, beyond life, it's late.

937
01:37:02,316 --> 01:37:04,341
I'll be with Vieira until the end.

938
01:37:07,587 --> 01:37:09,452
I can do nothing

939
01:37:11,291 --> 01:37:16,319
to avoid these
coming days of darkness.

940
01:37:18,899 --> 01:37:20,867
That's why I gave up.

941
01:37:23,570 --> 01:37:28,564
That's why I died!

942
01:37:30,911 --> 01:37:34,779
Democracy is the exercise
of the will of the people.

943
01:37:35,015 --> 01:37:40,920
We've been elected by the people,
so we' re representatives of their will.

944
01:37:41,154 --> 01:37:43,452
It's a time of decisions.

945
01:37:44,925 --> 01:37:48,827
The reactionaries will eat
the dust of history.

946
01:37:49,062 --> 01:37:52,395
Let's do our historical duty

947
01:37:52,632 --> 01:37:57,695
by forcing the President
to exterminate Vieira

948
01:37:57,938 --> 01:38:02,739
and his agents
all over Eldorado.

949
01:38:02,976 --> 01:38:07,936
I'll defend our wealth from
the foreign invader!

950
01:38:08,181 --> 01:38:13,483
God is my emblem!
Work is my flag!

951
01:38:13,720 --> 01:38:16,280
My destiny is happiness!

952
01:38:16,523 --> 01:38:20,755
My principle, purity of character!

953
01:38:20,994 --> 01:38:27,695
With strong arms, clean hands,
conscience at peace,

954
01:38:29,236 --> 01:38:32,228
we will build a great nation.

955
01:38:32,472 --> 01:38:35,930
The nation is untouchable!

956
01:38:36,176 --> 01:38:39,668
The family, sacred!

957
01:38:39,913 --> 01:38:44,407
My hope is the sunshine...

958
01:38:44,651 --> 01:38:48,417
Only one force can change history

959
01:38:48,655 --> 01:38:52,523
and nobody will stop it.

960
01:38:52,759 --> 01:38:55,455
This sunshine will light our lives.

961
01:38:55,695 --> 01:39:00,428
Dawn follows every night.
The mornings are never late!

962
01:39:00,667 --> 01:39:03,898
This strength, is the people.

963
01:39:06,673 --> 01:39:12,839
Vieira! Vieira!

964
01:39:31,598 --> 01:39:36,934
He is the people.
He is the people!

965
01:39:37,170 --> 01:39:42,472
The shining mornings, alive, eternal,

966
01:39:42,709 --> 01:39:48,841
everlasting, unchanging, infinite!

967
01:40:43,403 --> 01:40:44,700
Let's divide the country.

968
01:40:44,938 --> 01:40:47,304
If you say so, we'll bombard Eldorado.

969
01:40:48,742 --> 01:40:50,209
I don't care about bloodshed...

970
01:40:50,443 --> 01:40:52,343
I say!
The blood of the masses is sacred!

971
01:40:52,579 --> 01:40:54,376
It will be the beginning
of our history.

972
01:40:54,614 --> 01:40:56,844
If we fail, Diaz will rise to power.

973
01:40:57,083 --> 01:41:00,951
See Sara? Who was our leader?

974
01:41:02,789 --> 01:41:05,349
Our great leader?

975
01:41:05,592 --> 01:41:08,083
Obey my command.
Disperse any resistance!

976
01:41:11,765 --> 01:41:15,701
No more condecorations,

977
01:41:15,936 --> 01:41:18,928
this joyous pomp of glories.

978
01:41:19,172 --> 01:41:22,198
This golden hope on the Plateau.

979
01:41:22,442 --> 01:41:25,969
No more this regal parade

980
01:41:26,213 --> 01:41:29,444
with war and Christ
marching side by side!

981
01:41:29,683 --> 01:41:33,346
No more the impotence of faith,

982
01:41:33,587 --> 01:41:35,487
the naiveté of faith...

983
01:41:35,722 --> 01:41:38,452
It's no longer possible...

984
01:41:40,994 --> 01:41:43,428
We are eternal sons of darkness,

985
01:41:43,663 --> 01:41:45,597
of inquisition and conversion!

986
01:41:45,832 --> 01:41:48,892
And we are forever, sons of fear,

987
01:41:49,135 --> 01:41:52,161
of our brother's blood!

988
01:41:52,405 --> 01:41:54,532
And we don't accept our violence,

989
01:41:54,774 --> 01:41:56,639
we don't accept our ideas,

990
01:41:56,876 --> 01:42:00,368
neither our barbarian hate.

991
01:42:00,614 --> 01:42:02,912
We don't assume our stupid
and feeble past,

992
01:42:03,149 --> 01:42:07,085
plenty of prayers and laziness.

993
01:42:07,320 --> 01:42:10,983
A landscape,
a sound over indolent souls...

994
01:42:11,224 --> 01:42:15,991
These indolent races,
servile to God and the lords.

995
01:42:16,229 --> 01:42:19,995
A typical passive indolence
of indolent people.

996
01:42:20,233 --> 01:42:24,033
Ah, I can't believe it's all true!

997
01:42:24,271 --> 01:42:26,296
How long can we stand it?

998
01:42:26,539 --> 01:42:30,066
How long, beyond faith and hope,
can we stand it?

999
01:42:30,310 --> 01:42:34,246
Until when, beyond patience and love,
can we stand it?

1000
01:42:34,481 --> 01:42:37,382
Until when, oblivious to fear,

1001
01:42:37,617 --> 01:42:40,177
beyond childhood and adolescence,

1002
01:42:40,420 --> 01:42:42,217
can we stand it....

1003
01:42:49,729 --> 01:42:51,856
What does your death prove?

1004
01:42:52,098 --> 01:42:55,761
The triumph of beauty and justice!

1005
01:43:02,375 --> 01:43:05,606
They will learn! They will!

1006
01:43:05,845 --> 01:43:07,710
I will dominate this land.

1007
01:43:07,947 --> 01:43:11,110
I will put these hysterical
traditions in order!

1008
01:43:11,351 --> 01:43:15,515
By force,
by the "the love of force"!

1009
01:43:15,755 --> 01:43:19,623
By hell's universal harmony,

1010
01:43:19,859 --> 01:43:23,659
we will be a civilisation!

1011
01:43:36,543 --> 01:43:38,977
What does your death prove?

1012
01:43:39,212 --> 01:43:45,014
The triumph of beauty and justice!

